Commit, push, and ensure a PR exists. If the user provided a description, use it to drive the commit message and PR summary — skim the diff only to confirm and pick the right prefix. If no description, read the diff carefully to summarize the change. Either way, keep everything else mechanical.

## Steps

1. **Review**: run `git status`, `git diff`, `git diff --staged`, `git log --oneline -5` in parallel. Stop if on main/master or nothing to commit.
2. **Stage**: `git add` specific files (skip `.env`, `*.pem`, credentials). Never `git add -A`.
3. **Commit**: conventional commit — lowercase, imperative, no period, under 72 chars. No body — only the subject line and `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>` trailer.
4. **Push**: `git push -u origin HEAD`. Never force push.
5. **PR**: `gh pr view --json url 2>/dev/null` — if none exists, `gh pr create`. Title matches commit style. Body: `## Summary` (bullets), `## Test plan` (checklist), footer `🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)`. Base the summary on `git log main..HEAD`, not just the last commit.
6. **Report**: one line — what changed + PR URL.
